10 hours ago, kcs123 said:

IIRC, I reported clicktrough bug earlier (several weeks or even months ago) with exact described IR menu affected.
Not all of IR menus suffer from this, it is confirmed code oversight for this, but I can't give you exact link to post from top of my head is it in this thread or IR WIP part rework thread.

Clickthrough was fixed among other things in 2.0.7. Please retest.

8 hours ago, frencrs said:

Okay, IR 2.0.8, ModuleManager-2.7.4, fresh install with no other mods.

Log: https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B32vs_YxOWgjSDZaRHc0ZUVOMEU/view?usp=sharing

New game, create craft with IR parts attached, cheat into orbit around Kerbol past Eeloo, return to Space Center for 2-3 seconds, return to craft through tracking station. Is this kind of drift caused by a problem in the default game? I've seen Roverdude's USI Construction robotic parts drift like this using this same method.

Album of screenshots showing the drift:

http://imgur.com/a/qKlQh

Yes it problem with the game, and KSP fixes it by resetting all the part joints. Problem is that both Roverdude's USI and IR create their own joints that are unaffected by KSP's built in joint reset, leading to such problem. 

The similar problem was with timewarping in a Kerbol orbit, and it was fixed in 2.0.8, but your test case shows that there are more things to fix. I'll try to replicate and fix this one as well.

Clickthrough was fixed among other things in 2.0.7. Please retest.

Will do. However, my post was because of this:

18 hours ago, Ziw said:

The similar problem was with timewarping in a Kerbol orbit, and it was fixed in 2.0.8, but your test case shows that there are more things to fix. I'll try to replicate and fix this one as well.

 

Well there's a reason it was "DamnedRobotics" then "InfernalRobotics" and not "NiceRobotics" then "HeavenlyRobotics". Moveable joints in KSP are a huge PITA.
i tried to make a harrier... the Kraken likes it

I have the large boat parts mod installed and made my self an aircraft carrier. After timewarping on the carrier deck with my foldable-winged airplane the carrier itself starts twitching and exploding. Dont know how don't know why. 

http://imgur.com/a/TfLAc

The aircraft carrier doesn't have any parts from infernal robotics and i did apply the patch for KJR mentioned in this forum. Next to the carrier twitching, the turning point on the hinges flip causing my wings to go in the fuselage. 

Edited November 30, 2016 by ShiningNeedle

10 hours ago, ShiningNeedle said:

I have the large boat parts mod installed and made my self an aircraft carrier. After timewarping on the carrier deck with my foldable-winged airplane the carrier itself starts twitching and exploding. Dont know how don't know why. 

http://imgur.com/a/TfLAc

The aircraft carrier doesn't have any parts from infernal robotics and i did apply the patch for KJR mentioned in this forum. Next to the carrier twitching, the turning point on the hinges flip causing my wings to go in the fuselage. 

Logs would help. Also make sure you use version 2.0.8 of Infernal robotics
When will this be available through ckan for the latest ksp version?

1 hour ago, TacticalNuke7 said:

When will this be available through ckan for the latest ksp version?

With the current bugs - not anytime soon. If you want, you can install the latest version manually.
